cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CL, cs.DC, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a correspondence between classical logic and a functional language.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper defines a parallel extension of the simply typed lambda calculus.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant as the paper discusses communication mechanisms between processes.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper focuses on parallel programming.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses novel techniques for handling and transmitting process closures.
